## ðŸ“Š TECHNICAL ARCHITECTURE

### **Current Stack**

**Frontend:**
- Pure vanilla JavaScript (no frameworks)
- Modular architecture (ES6 imports)
- LocalStorage for data persistence
- GitHub Pages hosting (static site)

**File Structure:**
```
alongside/
  index.html
  js/
    app.js (orchestrator)
    store.js (state management)
    modules/
      onboarding.js
      checkin.js
      todayView.js
      workoutGenerator.js
      activeCoachFilters.js
      libraryLoader.js
      cards.js
      economy.js
  css/
    app.css (single file, all styles)
  data/
    library/
      index.json
      exercises/
        strength/ (bodyweight.json, dumbbell.json, etc)
        cardio/ (running.json, hiit.json, low-impact.json)
        mobility/ (stretching.json, yoga.json)
        recovery/ (breathing.json, mindfulness.json)
```

**Why This Stack:**
- âœ… No build process needed
- âœ… Fast deployment (GitHub Pages)
- âœ… Low cost (no server, no API calls)
- âœ… Privacy-first (all data local)
- âœ… Simple debugging
- âœ… Easy for Graeme to understand

---

### **When We'll Need Backend**

**Phase 3 requires:**
- User authentication
- Cross-device sync
- Payment processing
- Multi-user institutional accounts

**Options:**
1. **Firebase** (Google) - Easy auth, database, hosting
2. **Supabase** (open-source Firebase alternative) - Better pricing
3. **Custom Node.js backend** - More control, more work

**Recommendation:** Supabase (good balance of features and cost)

